    "This section systematically analyzes these three strategies, ordered by decreasing popularity, to elucidate the trade-offs, implementation architectures, and empirical results that define the current state of LLM-based test generation practice.To visually demonstrate the applicable scenarios and trade-offs of these three strategies, Table 1 provides a horizontal comparison regarding their resource requirements, data dependencies, and core advantages.",
    "Prompt EngineeringAs the dominant paradigm (89%), prompt engineering leverages general-purpose models by constructing context-rich inputs without modifying model parameters.",
    "The primary challenge lies in designing prompts that compensate for the model's lack of project context and domain-specific knowledge.",
    "A successful prompt for test generation must provide the LLM with sufficient information to construct a complete and valid test case.",
    "The design of such prompts can be decomposed into core components and the advanced techniques used to orchestrate them."
  ]
}